  "name": "novanet",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "module",
  "description": "NovaNet is a backend service that unifies astrophysical event data from multiple observatories — such as gravitational waves, optical flashes, and gamma-ray bursts. It ingests event data, standardizes it, and applies a correlation engine to detect linked cosmic events based on temporal (±1 day) and spatial (≤1° RA/DEC) proximity.",
